{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Articles and Tutorials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Exports","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Signals","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/CustomTypes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BindingNodes","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RunningInEditor"],"generated":true}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variants"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"article","title":"Variants","roleHeading":"Article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You will often find the type "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","isActive":true},{"text":" in Godot source code.   Variants are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Godot’s way of passing around certain data types.  They are similar to Swift’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Any"},{"text":" type, but they can only hold Godot types (most structures and classes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that derive from "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Creating Variant values","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Creating-Variant-values"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can create Variants from types that conform to the VariantStorable protocol.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This includes the following types:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Godot’s native types: GString, Vector, Rect, Transform, Plane, Quaternion,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AABB,  Basis, Projection, Int64, NodePaths, RIDs, Callable, GDictionary, Array","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and PackedArrays."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift types that SwiftGodot adds convenience conformances for: Bool, Int, String and Float","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Godot’s objects: e.g. Node, Area2D"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Other types that you can manually conform to VariantStorable."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You wrap your data type by calling one of the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"},{"text":" constructors, and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you can pass this variant to Godot functions that expect a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, to pass the value ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["let trueVaraint = Variant (true)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can get a string representation of a variant by calling ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/description","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["print (trueVariant.description)"]},{"anchor":"Extracting-values-from-Variants","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Extracting values from Variants"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you know the kind of return that a variant will return, you can invoke the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"failing initializer for that specific type for most structures. Every VariantStorable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will have an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(_ variant: Variant)"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, this is how you could get a Vector2 from a variant:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func distance (variant: Variant) -> Float? {","    guard let vector = Vector2 (variant) else {","\treturn nil","    }","    return vector.length ()","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Notice that this might return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", which would be the case if the variant","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"contains a different type than the one you were expecting. You can check the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type of the variant by accessing the "},{"code":".gtype","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the variant."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Extracting Godot-derived objects from Variants","type":"heading","anchor":"Extracting-Godot-derived-objects-from-Variants"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Godot-derived objects are slightly different. If you know you have a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject"},{"type":"text","text":" stored in the variant, you can call the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/asObject(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instead.  This is a generic method, so you would invoke it like this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func getNode (variant: Variant) -> Node? {","    guard let node = variant.asObject<Node> ()) else {","\t  return nil","    }","    return node","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reason to have a method rather than a constructor is that this method will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"make sure that only one instance of your objects is surfaced to Swift."}]},{"anchor":"Accessing-Array-Elements","text":"Accessing Array Elements","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some of the variant types contain arrays, either objects, or a particular","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"packed version of those.   You can access the individual elements of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"those with a convenient subscript provided on the array."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Calling Variant Methods","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Calling-Variant-Methods"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is possible to invoke the built-in variant methods that exist in the Godot"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"universe by using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"call"},{"text":" method on a Variant.   This is very similar to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"call method on an Object.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, you can invoke this generic “size” method on an array to get the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"size of an array, regardless of the specific type of array:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func printSize (myArray: Variant) {","    switch variant.call(method: \"size\") {","    case .failure(let err):","        print (err)","        return 0","    case .success(let val):","        return Int (val) ?? 0","    }","}"]}]}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Follow up on the fundamental building block of Godot’s data types.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variants"]}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Differences":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/differences","title":"SwiftGodot API differences to GDScript","role":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This document lists some common differences between GDSscript and SwiftGodot."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Differences","kind":"article"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/GodotObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","title":"GodotObject","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/godotobject","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol implemented by the built-in classes in Godot to allow to be wrapped in a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GodotObject","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GodotObject","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Variant/asObject(_:)":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/asObject(_:)","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/variant\/asobject(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"Attempts to cast the Variant into a GodotObject, if the variant contains a value of type ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".object"},{"type":"text","text":", then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"code":".object, the value ","ty